Wash and dry produce. Dice @Tomato{1} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Halve and toast @Brioche Buns{2}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Cream Sauce Base{4%ounce}, @Cream Cheese{4%tablespoon}, and half the @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings) over medium heat. Cook, whisking, until smooth and thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Taste and season with a pinch of @Salt{} and @Pepper{} if desired. Remove pot from heat; cover to keep warm.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large, preferably nonstick, pan{} over medium heat. Once hot, crack @Eggs{4} into pan and cover. (TIP: Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.) Fry eggs to preference. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

While eggs cook, in a #large bowl{}, toss @Mixed Greens{2%ounce} and tomato with as much @Creamy Balsamic Dressing{1.5%ounce} as you like.

Divide toasted buns, cut sides up, between plates; top each bun half with a folded @Prosciutto{2%ounce} slice, one egg, and as much Hollandaise sauce as you like.

Serve eggs Benedict with salad on the side.

> Wash hands and surfaces after handling raw eggs. Consuming raw or undercooked eggs may increase your risk of foodborne illness.